        <div class="row">

             <div class="col-md-3">
                <p class="lead">Ingredients</p>
                 <ul class="list-group">
                  <li class="list-group-item">
                    <span class="badge">12 ounces</span>
                    Salmon fillet
                  </li>
                  <li class="list-group-item">
                    <span class="badge">1/2 tbsp</span>
                    Coarse-grained salt
                  </li>
                  <li class="list-group-item">
                    <span class="badge">2 tbsp</span>
                    Freshly ground black pepper
                  </li>
                  <li class="list-group-item">
                    <span class="badge">2</span>
                    Baked squash
                  </li>
                                         
                </ul>

                <p class="lead">Additional Images</p>
                <%= image_tag "blackpepper.jpg", :class => 'img-responsive image-spacing'%>

            </div>

            <div class="col-md-9">

                <div class="thumbnail">
                    <%= image_tag "salmon.jpg", :class => 'img-responsive'%>
                    <div class="caption-full">
                        <h3 class = "header-spacing"Oven-Baked Salmon</h3>
                    </div>

                        <p class = "p-spacing">Salmon health benefits range from strengthening your muscles and heart to reducing your chances of developing some diseases. Studies have shown that consumption of the fatty acid rich salmon can help you live longer and be healthier while you do it. </p>

              </div>
              <div class = "thumbnail">
                    <div class="caption-full">
                        <h3>Preparation Instructions
                        </h3>
                        <em>Total Time: 20 minutes</em>
                    </div>

              <ol class = "preparation-instructions">
                  <li>
                  Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F.
                  </li>
                  <li>Season salmon with salt and pepper. Place salmon, skin side down, on a non-stick baking sheet or in a non-stick pan with an oven-proof handle. </li>
                  <li>Bake until salmon is cooked through, about 12 to 15 minutes. </li>
                  <li>Serve with squash, if desired.</li>
                  
                </ol>

                </div>

